Analysis of data exploration

Preparation for modeling

Data preparation

As we started knowing the dataset more, we identified some relationship between the predictors. We applied that knowledge and model performance together to modify the list variables used in the models. Our goal was to keep the model parsimonious. We removed the columns which we thought unnecessary for modeling.

# Remove the columns which have least impact to the model
housedata$date = NULL
#housedata$sqft_lot = NULL
#housedata$sqft_lot15 = NULL
#housedata$yr_built = NULL
housedata$lat = NULL
housedata$long = NULL
housedata$id = NULL
#housedata$sqft_basement = NULL

Outlier handling

Explain each of these

# outliers from Gleb
housedata <- housedata[housedata$bedrooms != 33, ]
housedata <- housedata[housedata$bathrooms != 0, ]
housedata$sqft_basement <- ifelse(housedata$sqft_basement >0 ,1,0)
housedata$yr_renovated <- ifelse(housedata$yr_renovated >0 ,1,0)
x<-quantile(housedata$price,c(0.01,0.99))

housedata <- housedata[housedata$price >=x[1] & housedata$price<=x[2],]

Handling of invalid values

Transformation

# transformations from Gleb
housedata$price <- log(housedata$price)
housedata$sqft_living <- log(housedata$sqft_living)
housedata$sqft_above <- log(housedata$sqft_above)
housedata$sqft_living15 <- log(housedata$sqft_living15)
housedata$sqft_lot <- log(housedata$sqft_lot)
housedata$sqft_lot15 <- log(housedata$sqft_lot15)

Derived variables

housedata$yr_built <- 2019 - housedata$yr_built

Model validation

We partitioned the dataset into an 75/25 training/test split.

=========

# split samples (75% for training and 25% for testing)
select.myd <- sample(1:nrow(housedata), 0.75*nrow(housedata))
#Selecting 75% of the data for training purpose
train.myd <- housedata[select.myd,]
#Selecting 25% (remaining) of the data for testing
test.myd <- housedata[-select.myd,]

Model building process

We started with linear regression model using the full dataset. Then we ran several iterations of modeling. We built best subset, forward, backward and stepwise models.

Best model subset selection DSawh: removed all sqr foot for 2015 and zip code

set.seed(998)
library(leaps)
best_subset <- regsubsets(price ~bedrooms+bathrooms+sqft_living+sqft_lot+floors+as.factor(waterfront)+as.factor(view)+as.factor(condition)+grade+sqft_above+as.factor(sqft_basement)+yr_built+as.factor(yr_renovated), train.myd)

                      as.factor(view) + sqft_living+ 
                      floors + as.factor(condition) + bedrooms + as.factor(waterfront), data = train.myd)

Create fitted values using test.myd data

y_pred <- predict.glm(fit2, test.myd)
y_obs<-test.myd[,"price"]

Compute RMSE of prediction errors

rmse_m1_bestset <- sqrt((y_obs - y_pred)%*%(y_obs - y_pred)/nrow(test.myd))
rmse_m1_bestset
##           [,1]
## [1,] 0.3042539

Compute mean absolute error

mae_m1_bestset <-mean(abs(y_obs - y_pred))
mae_m1_bestset
## [1] 0.242581

Compute mean percentage absolute error

mape_m1_bestset <-mean(abs((y_obs - y_pred)/y_obs))*100
mape_m1_bestset
## [1] 1.867602
